JOHANNESBURG - SAA on Monday cancelled flights to the United States due to the bad weather conditions as a result of winter storm, Stella.Flights are those to and from the Washington, DC and New York have been affected.Winter storm, Stella is expected to affect parts of America until Tuesday.SAA says it will monitor the situation and reinstate its schedule once it's safe to operate.The airline advised travellers to check the SAA website for updates and cancellations.Last month the airline also cancelled flights to New York due to bad weather, for the second time this year already.READ: SAA cancels flights between New York and JohannesburgeNCA